		<div id="comment_body_64122981"><p><div class="quote"><p>By your logic what we do today will decide 2044?</p></div><p>Yes. What we do today decides if in 2044 the trend in temperature increase will go up, stay the same, or go down.<br>Even if you magically stop ALL emissions today or if we go full-throttle on fossil fuels burning, the IPCC scenarios are the same for the next 20 years (first order approximation).</p><p>During the COVID pandemic, the levels of CO2 decreased by ~5%. The actual impact on climate change was negligible. If we want to have some kind of impact, we would need 5% reduction in emissions <i>every year</i> (on top of th<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
